HEPATITIS A - RUSSIA (PSKOV)
****************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 26 Oct 2004
From: Russian ProMED-mail correspondent Natalya Pchenitchnaia
<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Rambler.ru news agency, Russia, 26 Oct 2004
[in Russian, translated by Mod.NR; edited]
<http://www.rambler.ru/db/news/msg.html?s=7&mid=5198692>

The number of hepatitis patients has increased to 130 in Pskov (Russia)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
3 more people with a diagnosis of viral hepatitis A were hospitalized
yesterday [25 Oct 2004] in Pskov. This report came from the Emergency
Situations Ministry (ESM). "We have 130 people, including 52 children, who
are being treated. [Yesterday we] hospitalized 3 people and discharged 5
children," declared a representative of ESM. An Emergency Situation was
declared due to the increased risk of viral hepatitis A. According to
preliminary investigations, it is possible that the source of infection is
the town water canal network, and also springs and wells situated in one of
the regions of the town.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
